A comic book series written by Duffy Boudreau and illustrated by Wendell Cavalcanti and Antonio Fabela.

The story is about a future society that lives in a self-sufficent city-state called Blackacre, the mother of all gated communities, developed by ultra-wealthy businessmen, security contractors, and political gurus. Outside the city walls are the Hinterlands and its hostile population. Captain Hull is sent out to find a man called Greene who recently disappeared.

description:
Graphin novel published in 2012.

After the events depicted in Kade: Identity, Nieves returns home to her icy kingdom of Veserun to find it in turmoil. The death of Apollyon has sent ripples of evil throughout the world, awakening the ancient demon Malkoth, imprisoned in the ice for thousands of years. His power weakened, but still potent, Malkoth's corrupting influence forces the ice elves to free him. The only one that stands against him is Nieves!
